26/03/2007
ANKARA Turkey -- Prosecutors have ordered the arrest of a Turkish nationalist politician in connection with the January murder of Turkish Armenian journalist Hrant Dink. Local media reported that Yasar Cihan, head of the Trabzon branch of the Great Unity Party, was detained for questioning on Sunday (March 25th). Police are also looking for another prominent member of the party, Halis Egemen. 
Dink, editor of the bilingual newspaper Agos, was gunned down in front of his office in Istanbul. Ten suspects have been arrested in connection with the killing, including former members of the Great Unity Party's youth organisation. (AP - 25/03/07) 
